<h2>My Van Build</h2>
<p>I'm by no means an over-sharer so my apologies for not having detailed videos and walkthroughs of my van build. I do however have a bunch of photos I took along the way which should help give a little context to my explainations. I'll give a brief rundown of my van build and a few pictures as i go however <a href="https://photos.app.goo.gl/HYozABbLFWVFPpwU9" target="_blank">here</a> is a link to my google photos where i uploaded all the van pics that i took</p>

<p>In the summer of 2019 I bought the van after another employee/friend of mine had a vehicle break down and I was put in a situation where i would need to hire a new technician or make the leap to buy a van and let him use my vehicle. After dreaming of vanlife for over a year i was ready to do it but was too scared to pull the trigger. His unfortunate vehicle trouble was just the push I needed to finally commit! </p>

<p>A week went by while i frantically searched dealerships nearby to no avail. I expanded my search to the next state over and finally started seeing what i was looking for. I called the dealership and made sure they had the van in stock and told them I was booking a flight the next day to go get it. When I flew in, someone from the dealership picked me up at the airport and drove me to the dealership where I test drove and proceeded to go through with the purchase. It was a 10 hour drive to get back to where I was living at the time but I couldn't stop smiling the whole way back!</p>

<p>I had MY van!!! It was used but in good enough condition and low enough mileage that i shouldn't have issues for a long time! I got my hands on a 2018 Ram Promaster 2500 136" Wheelbase. My job had me working </p>
