<p>The time had come to start putting in some serious overtime to turn this empty shell into something habitable. Since I was building this thing from floor to ceiling I figured I would need to first lay some groundwork.... I laid down some reflectix, which in theory should have helped with reflecting under carriage heat(this may or not have even been beneficial but when it comes to insulation the more the better). On top of the reflectix I installed 3/4" plywood as my main flooring element. What I did next I wouldn't recommend because while it hasn't caused an issue yet, I feel like it could be an issue down the road... I got some metal tapping screws and screwed the plywood directly to the base of the van. If I were to do it all over again i would have removed the reflectix and simply glued the plywood directly to the van (every hole you make is one more spot for potential rust) </p>
