<p>Next, I found some peel and stick vinyl floor tiles which installed super easily, and were cheap enough that I told myself when one gets damaged I can just replace the tile. This decision was one I ended up regretting later as the tiles would shrink and swell massively depending on the temperature or if they were caught in direct sunlight. 2 years later I ended up ripping out those cheap peel and stick tiles and replacing them with interlocking vinyl planks. They are far more durable, don't expand nearly as bad in the sun, and look a lot better than the peel and stick tiles. The price difference was only like $20 more expensive (total) than it was for the peel and stick tiles... I only needed 1 box (its only like a 6x10 foot space after all!). Since all of the firniature and cabinets were already in place, I only had to replace the section in the open which drastically cut down on the cost </p>

