<p>The next thing i tackled was insulation. When i first started looking for insulation ideas i found a few van build videos that used Rigid Foam Board insulation and since it was readily available at the local hardware store and i didn't want to wait around for something to ship to me i decided to go that route. Foam board has a decent R-value and is fairly easy to install. The process I would follow is:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Cut out the foam board to fit into the next wall cavity</li>
    <li>Add some spray foam to the side that touched the van and around the outside edges of the board</li>
    <li>Brace a board against it for 30+ mins while to sprayfoam dried enough to stay put (they say you need 12-24 hours for the spray foam to fully cure but when used as an adhesive it held up the foam board just fine)</li>
    <li>Rinse and repeat</li>
</ol>
